<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF99FFB7C9F5FEB6FD84B6E8" blockId="12.[136,1452,265,652]" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF99FFB7C9F5FEB6FE13B5F4" bold="true" box="[189,429,373,400]" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF99FFB7C8E5FEB5FD7BB5F4" authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1860" box="[429,709,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="potentilloides">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF99FFB7C8E5FEB5FD7BB5F4" box="[429,709,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">Euphorbia potentilloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically diverse, but this variation is restricted mostly to the vegetative characteristics (leaves and cyathophylls; see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF952FDFFF99FFB7CA0DFE59FBD1B5D0" author="Simmons, M. P. &amp; Hayden, W. J." box="[837,1135,410,436]" pageId="12" pageNumber="205" pagination="155 - 180" refId="ref11773" refString="Simmons, M. P. &amp; Hayden, W. J. (1997) Revision of the cerrado hemicryptophytic Chamaesyce of Boissier's &quot; Pleiadeniae &quot; (Euphorbiaceae). Brittonia 49: 155 - 180. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 2807678" type="journal article" year="1997">Simmons &amp; Hayden 1997</bibRefCitation>
). The species may be easily recognized among the others species with interpetiolar stipules, opposite leaves and cyathial glands with petaloid appendages occurring in the State of 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF99FFB7CB64FE21FD20B598" box="[556,670,482,508]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
because it is the only one with cyathia arranged in pleiochasia. Also, the species may bear up to 7 cyathial glands (although in 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF99FFB7CA45FDC5FC06B644" box="[781,952,518,544]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">São Paulo state</collectingRegion>
only specimens with up to 6 cyathial glands were observed) and has smooth seeds, a characteristic found only on 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF99FFB7CADFFDE9FBD3B620" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1817" box="[919,1133,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpens">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF99FFB7CADFFDE9FBD3B620" box="[919,1133,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">Euphorbia serpens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by its erect stem (vs. prostrate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF99FFB7C8F7FD8CFD88B60C" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1817" box="[447,566,591,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpens">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF99FFB7C8F7FD8CFD88B60C" box="[447,566,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">E. serpens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), linear to narrowly elliptic leaves (
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF99FFB7CA98FD8CFC51B60C" box="[976,1007,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">vs.</emphasis>
orbicular in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF99FFB7CDCBFD8CFB44B60C" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1817" box="[1155,1274,591,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpens">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF99FFB7CDCBFD8CFB44B60C" box="[1155,1274,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">E. serpens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and cyathia in pleiochasia (vs. solitary in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF99FFB7C8FDFDB0FD94B6E8" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1817" box="[437,554,627,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpens">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF99FFB7C8FDFDB0FD94B6E8" box="[437,554,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="205">E. serpens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
